This paper deals with the problem of uniquely decodable code pairs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorial and algorithmic techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic arguments and analysis, which could place it under cs.SI (social and information networks) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
